<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-80D53CA7-611A-4EEC-9FAA-0F44C8811C9D" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-80D53CA7-611A-4EEC-9FAA-0F44C8811C9D" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">11 Troubleshooting installation USB key creation issues</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M140828-B205"><p class="- topic/p ">When you create an installation USB key for the system, the following error message can show at the end of the process. 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-BD6DA82E-D8C6-4379-A502-3D35429B166B"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-DD37F1AD-04E5-422C-A7FA-3F79A142A4C1-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-DD37F1AD-04E5-422C-A7FA-3F79A142A4C1-low.png"/></fig></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M140828-B207" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The logfile</title><p class="- topic/p ">The CreateUSB application generates a log file (CreateUSB.CreateUSB_&lt;date&gt;.log) that can help to find the cause of the error. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Open the log file (Log &gt; Open log file): 
</p><fig id="GUID-9D3D2179-044B-4306-8241-7CE190DC893B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BDE20787-D2A3-4C47-9B5A-39D0DB17BF3A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BDE20787-D2A3-4C47-9B5A-39D0DB17BF3A-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">A log file is displayed as a text file. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Possible causes are, depending on the content of the log file. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Below we describe 2 possible problems that are most common. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_8B2EDF5F2405440097F73F1429FA79F0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The USB cannot be ejected</title><p class="- topic/p ">As an example, the log file contents the following text strings: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">24/01/2017 12:06:48 THD:17 USB disk F: failed to eject, returnvalue: WindowsService 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">24/01/2017 12:06:48 THD:17 Destroy USB Stick so it can't boot and will not start install service check 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">24/01/2017 12:06:49 THD:17 Volume of USB disk F:\ successfully changed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">24/01/2017 12:07:32 THD:17 USB Installation Key creation has failed. 
</p><table id="GUID-44E51CAE-2EF5-431B-BFBB-AE0F0810C645" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Search for “failed to eject” text string 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If the string is present, close CreateUSB and the displayed log file. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Restart CreateUSB and try again. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If it fails again, use another key. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-90644E1B-4B92-419B-8CFB-B35412CDCB87" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The key is not writable (for security purpose)</title><p class="- topic/p ">As an example, the log file contents the following text strings: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">13/02/2017 10:54:47 THD:7 A USB prepare actions has failed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">13/02/2017 10:54:47 THD:7 Destroy USB Stick so it can't boot and will not start install service check 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">13/02/2017 10:54:49 THD:7 USBHandling.ChangeVolumeName threw an exception: System.UnauthorizedAccessException: Volume labels can only be set for writable local volumes. 
</p><table id="GUID-06DC6FA6-FF85-4665-80B3-41C1E24F0F7F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Search for “writable local volumes” text string 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If the string is present, check if the key is writable. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use File Explorer to copy a file to the key 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If it fails, use another key. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-52AC0B80-9752-46D4-B024-EBDD1101329A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
